HEADWORD: Renne
<hw>Ren"ne</hw> <pr>(r?n"n<it>e</it>)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
plunder; -- only in the phrase ⟦ldquo⟧to rape and
<xex>renne</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ See under <er>Rap</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, to
snatch.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Renne</ent>⟦br⟧

